\begin{flushleft}
\acrshort{qos} is a primary mechanism for managing congestion and ensuring reliable delivery of content to all users. \textbf{Congestion} occurs when the demand for bandwidth exceeds the amount available. \textbf{Network bandwidth} is measured in \textit{bits per second}(bps), the number of bits that can be transmitted in a single second. \textbf{Priority queue policy} is implemented by routers if the network experiences congestion.
\end{flushleft}
